[Placeholder describing the 2x2 factorial experimental design.
 Treatment 1 (Lactoscan): Cluster-randomized provision of a quality measurement
 and digital monitoring system---a Lactoscan milk analyzer combined with
 a digitalized bookkeeping application that records quality readings across
 deliveries and over time---to MCCs.
 This bundled intervention enables both point-of-delivery quality measurement
 and systematic quality tracking, making quality not just visible but traceable
 and trackable.
 Treatment 2 (Video): Farmer-level randomization of a quality awareness
 video within all MCCs.
 The design allows estimation of the individual and joint effects of supply-side
 information (video) and demand-side quality infrastructure (measurement
 plus digital monitoring).]
